&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I would prefer a Knight at that level, because the Warrior's just aren't able to hold the aggro as fast, which is needed. I also like the fact that both knights are able to stop the mob from running away (at those levels) to fast. At 66, there is no Call of Challenge, and well..... What AA's from Oman's are you suggesting he should have?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If the Knight was around the same level, what AA's did he have that the Warrior most likely didn't have? These are question's that always come to my mind when seeing a post from someone that just assume's there was something wrong with the person playing the class, then the class itself. Warrior's are fixed for level 75, and alot better at level 70, but broken as heck from level 45 to 65, and pretty bad off in the levels of 66 to 69.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bassically, all is well if you just level up. This is not easy for other class's to understand. You can play your Caster, healer, buffer, DPS class just fine if you emphasize your gear on what matter's most (DPS with weapons, and AA's to enhance, Healer with Healer AA's, and gear to enhance, Knight's with AA's to enhance their special skills, and gear to enhance, although moreso reliant on better all around gear then the other's). However, A Warrior get's skills after level 69 that they just do not possess at all before this level. This is a fact of the game, and warrior's although seemingly "fixed" (Dropped out of discussion's almost entirely on issue's concerning them, FOR A WHILE NOW), are broke as much as ever at lower level's, even moreso in today's game.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
