&lt;DIV&gt;I just wanted to air a few things out.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Seems to me, that most discussions on this board, are refering to the HIGH end gear warriors.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What if we for a few minutes took a look at the mid end gear warriors tanking ?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I currently have a 66 warrior with 50somthing(forgot exact amount) of AA's, and working to improve this.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I currently sit with 6.7/8K hp and around then 1300ac mark(Unbuffed)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;My point of this post is that, at the progression I am at (Missing very few kills till EP'ed). I have been in situations where I have been "taken" out of the role I held in my group,&amp;nbsp; take for example a time in WoS,&amp;nbsp;there was a knight (SK) that could take over tanking THOUGH havnig less HP / AC then me (I was sitting at 9000hp/1500 ac, and he was sat at 8.2K/1400AC), and the cleric actually insisted to the point (was groupleader) That I stepped down as tank, and let the SK overtake, or left the group.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This to me, seems rather unbalancing, when a cleric actually ask's a inferior(Hp/AC) tank, to take over tanking, when no issues were being had with other tank (Hell, we had slaughtered 3-5 nameds in WoS, before the SK came into the picture, without a problem)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Am I the only one who has experienced this sort of happening ? Or have I just been unlucky?(Happened 6-7 times to me now)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If there is anything I can improve let me know. I have done my very best to be able to cope with handling my responsibilty as a tank, even though I am NO WAY near the high end equipment. Due to being at work (And the firewall is blocking me to get to my magelo, I will be posting it once I get home later today)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But any feedback of what I might have been doing wrong or what I can improve, will be very much appreciated!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Well first few things Id ask is this, one how did the SK perform ? Secondly was the SK guilded with the same guild as the cleric ?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Third Was the SK higher level than you ? Because in some respects levels DO matter,&amp;nbsp; because higher level does mean there is a better chance of not taking huge damage. Anyone can tell the difference between a level 50 war and a level 70. Gets more difficult in 4 to 5 level differences. And also I know that your painting the picture of being the victum here and many folks do, but no one can be sure of the situation in a one sided discussion. I personally have been on the oppisite side of this situation. Group I knew realized I was online they had an SK of a much higher level than I was at the time.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The sk had real personality problems IE:Jerk and they decided to tell him they were all tired and going to break group. They did in fact the 2 minutes it took me to get to there location. The sk did know he was replaced by me and he probably thought that it was the groups loss, but in reality not all folks personalities match. This may have been the situation and the cleric placed whom they felt they could work with more easily in that role. This is one of hundreds of different situations it could be with the little information we have, stats matter for tanking, but not always for whom does a role.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The only real advice anyone can give is to level, but the advice i would give is to strive to be a person easy going and adaptive to situations. I group pretty regularly with SK's,PAL yes if im mt I do strive to be tanking most things, but if they tell me there bored and want to do those responsibilies. Its just xp, I ask the cleric if there ok with it sure they can do it, Pulling gets boring and were both tank classes. And it allows me time to keep myself current with pulling mobs, a skill many people should strive to learn.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
