&lt;P&gt;Hi Fild,&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I think all of us are faced from time to time with discriminatory groupmates.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In the scenario you described, there's a ton of reasons the cleric could've acted as he did, none of it having to do with you, or your abilities/playstyle/class.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Let me give some examples:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1. He could've been friends with the SK&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2. He could've grouped several times with the SK and become comfortable with him.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3. He could just be a not very informed guy, or nervous or jittery about aggro, and felt better with a SK for that reason.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;There's plenty of reasons someone would choose one tank over another, and a small difference in durability isn't necessarily the only thing that folks look for.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; My advice is, keep doing your best, don't get annoyed and lash out over something like this, and go with the flow, pull out your best DPS weapons and go to town.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
